Hermit
,
as if suddenly recalled to the duty on which
he had come to the convent, turned and glided away.
The porter, who had received his instructions
relative
to him for whom the mass was to be said,
offered
no further obstacle, but permitted Ilse to
conduct
her mistress within. No sooner were the
females
in the court, than he closed and barred the
